metadata.name: Henoheno Samurai #56
metadata.description:
This work was inspired by Otsu-e(Â§ßÊ¥•Áµµ), a Japanese painting in the Edo period. Otsu-e were inexpensive paintings made as souvenirs. Although mass-produced using paper stencils, the artisans painted by hand, resulting in variations in the quality of their work. Connoisseurs found them interesting and collected them as works of art. Otsu-e showed a new value of beauty in Japanese art, different from Ukiyo-e (ÊµÆ‰∏ñÁµµ) which are prints, and from fine art paintings which are one-of-a-kind artworks.

This work is made of canvas2D Bezier curves. Not just a combination of parts, but also a random displacement of the Bezier curve points to lose the shape. This is intended to create fun with the Otsu-e-like effect.


Features:
This profile is made up of 8 parts (brows, eyes, nose, mouth, ear, contour, hair, and body). Each part has 100 basic types. 
There are 7 skin colors and 12 kimono colors. Each RGB value of the colors is randomly added within a range of ¬±10. In addition, there are 70 kimono patterns. 
The distortion rate due to displacement of Bezier curve points is 0.0~50.0. 


BTW The title "Henoheno" is taken from the Japanese character picture "Henohenomoheji" known since the Edo period.

ARAUCO is a tribute to araucarias and Mapuche iconography. Incorporating elements such as the Kultrung, the W√ºnelfe star, and the staggered cross Ng√ºmin, the work displays a typical landscape of southern Chile with the Andes Mountains in the background and the native forest.

metadata.name: Floatrest #226
metadata.description:
Floating forests over the endless sky, where birds, trees, plants, roots, rocks and waterfalls share an ecosystem full of life and emotion.

You can see some rain clouds in the sky and the sun shining under the raindrops.

The earth is moving, the blocks are falling, but the trees are strong in their roots.

Welcome to 'Floatrest'.

----

# Features

- 7 tree palettes
- 17 different background colors
- 10 different terrain colors
- clouds
- vines
- roots
- plants
- waterfall
- birds
- sun / moon
- night
- dark mode
- monochromatic
- 2 different aspect ratios (square & portrait)

This artwork requires processing power and is intended for laptops and desktops primarily. It may take some time to render.

----

July 2022, gpitombo

metadata.name: Curlida #188
metadata.description:
Fully generative art. Each token is 100% unique.

Traits:
- 28 color palettes;
- 5 "stylers" - cells filling style;
- 3 "ratio" - aspect ratio.

Press 's' to save png.

High-level description of the algorithm:
Frame is separated into flows using several different Perlin noise generators. 
Frame cells are filled with curves. Each curve is drawn in the direction plotted by noise generator.
Each value returned by the generator at (x, y) is mapped to color from a predefined range.


Made with p5js, math and love by @ivposure

metadata.name: Mei(Ê¢Ö) #175
metadata.description:
Mei(Ê¢Ö):

"Mei" is an oriental art piece featuring the imagery of plum blossom, a symbol of courage and perseverance in traditional Chinese culture.

The generative system at the backend of "Mei" is an exploration of this cultural symbol by modern art language. The basic elements of the paintings are merely circles and enclosed flow field shapes. A great variety of short and light strokes of such elements are used across the paintings. Xuan paper is occasionally used as background, which is a painting material since the Tang dynasty.

Mei's outputs span different stages of plum blossom from winter to spring. The scene also changes from a calm day to snowy or even stormy weather. The consistent yet complex senses and feelings reflected are surprisingly versatile.

metadata.name: Con(text)ual #68
metadata.description:
Con(text)ual is a generative painting made from ASCII characters confined into shapes. Shapes are randomly drawn onto the canvas, then filled with individual characters from a character array. The density of characters is dependent upon the size of the shape, creating some transparencies and an organic feel to each shape.

I've long been interested in typography as an artform and this is an extension of my typography explorations.

There are a total of 10 color pallets. The number of shapes on each canvas varies from 3 to 9. The edition size was chosen based on the code, which lends itself well to a wide array of potential outcomes. Please get in touch with me if you want a larger resolution size for printing. 

I hope you enjoy the art!

Made with 100% Code and p5.js
Licensed under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0

metadata.name: Cold materials #10
Cold materials #36
Mooncakes: Happy Mid Autumn Festival 2022 #1632
metadata.description:
To celebrate the Moon Festival with Mooncakes, we have created a quest to introduce everyone to fxhash. As part of that quest on mooncakes.fun, users are encouraged to mint this generative token.

This is a layered image composition using the Mooncakes site images on a 1920x1080 canvas. The image elements are randomly assigned position, scale, tint, and blur according to a ruleset which generates a Mid Autumn Festival scene made up of: Moon, Clouds, Stars, Lanterns, and Lotuses.

Special filters, shapes and colors are included as rare features, as well as a couple of surprises.

metadata.name: Acequia #206
metadata.description:
Acequia (‚Äúah-seh-kee-uh‚Äù) - a Spanish adaptation of the Arabic word as-sƒÅqiya, meaning ‚Äúwater carrier‚Äù. 

In our second collaboration, Rich and Rick are back with our blend of generative code, intricate design, attention to detail, and a splash of charm. 

‚Ä®Acequias are traditional irrigation canals used to distribute rainwater and snowmelt along a complex network of narrow channels. They are found in Spain, the American Southwest, and northern Mexico, where they are essential for sustaining fields, orchards, and gardens in semi-arid regions. ‚Ä®‚Ä®
Our aim in this series is to capture the essence of these waterways in bold geometric designs. Each piece is inspired by a mountain village or town in Andalusia (southern Spain). 

The location determines the cube designs and construction rules that are used to build the final output. These are combined with striking day/night palettes, outline styles, scales, climates, and a few surprises of course!


Controls (in live view): 

- Press [p] to pause water animation 
- Press [e] to complete water animation 
- Press [r] to reset water animation 
- Press [s] to save the current image 
- Press [h] for a high-res output suitable for printing 
- Press [b] to toggle the border
